According to the "Report on Human Rights Violations in the U.S. 2020," people of color account for about one-third of the U.S. minors under the age of 18, but they account for two-thirds of the total number of incarcerated minors. The COVID-19 infection rate among citizens of African descent is three times that of whites, the death rate is twice that of whites, and the probability of being killed by the police is three times that of whites. In this episode, Adam, a New Yorker, tells the story of being an African American in the U.S. He also shares his thoughts on the racism embedded in the system.